《财经》杂志官方微信。
An official letter from Caijing magazine.
《财经》杂志由中国证券市场研究中心主办，1998年创刊，秉承“独立、独家、独到”的新闻理念，以权威性、公正性、专业性报道见长，是政经学界决策者、研究者、管理者的必读刊物。
"Caijing" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was founded in 1998, upholding the news concept of "independence, exclusivity and originality," and providing authoritative, impartial and professional reports.
。
.
如果新型冠状肺炎疫情成为全球性的大流行病，经济衰退就难以避免。
If the new outbreak of coronary pneumonia becomes a global pandemic, a recession is inevitable.
在接下来的几周里，美欧股市可能还会有更多糟糕的日子。
There are likely to be more bad days ahead for US and European stock markets in the coming weeks.
2月28日中国沪深A股和中国香港股市开盘后，亦出现较大幅度的下跌文 |《财经》特派记者金焱发自华盛顿 编辑 | 苏琦近期新型冠状病毒在世界六大洲蔓延多日后，终于在2月27日成为影响全球经济走势的主要叙事，美欧股市当天全面下跌。
China's Shanghai and Shenzhen A-shares and Hong Kong, China, also fell sharply after the stock markets opened on Feb. 28. Yan Jin, a New Coronavirus from Washington, D.C., recently spread over six continents, finally became the dominant story affecting the global economy on February 27, when US and European stocks fell across the board.
2月28日中国沪深A股和中国香港股市开盘后，亦出现较大幅度的下跌。
Shares in Shanghai and Shenzhen, China, and Hong Kong, China, also fell sharply after the market opened on February 28.
尽管美国总统特朗普当地时间2月26日表示，新冠病毒在美国的扩散不是“不可避免的”，目前美国面临的风险“仍然很低”。
Although US President Donald Trump said on February 26 that the spread of the virus in the United States is not "inevitable," the risks facing the United States are "still very low."
但悲观情绪继续主导美国金融市场，市场更倾向于相信卫生安全专家的警示，美国目前已经处于一种新的大流行病的早期，医学界尚无法预期这种病毒的致死率到底是多高。
But pessimism continues to dominate US financial markets, and markets are more likely to believe the warnings of health-safety experts that the US is in the early stages of a new pandemic and that the medical community cannot yet predict how high the virus will kill.
美东时间2月27日美股收盘延续前几天的大幅下跌，三大股指均跌逾4%，其中道指重挫近1200点。
Feb. 27 U.S. stocks ended down sharply in the days before, with all three indexes down more than 4%, with the Dow dropping nearly 1,200 points.
截止收盘，道指跌4.42%，纳斯达克指数跌4.61%，标普500指数跌4.42%。
By the close, the Dow was down 4.42%, the Nasdaq was down 4.61% and the S & P 500 was down 4.42%.
美国三大股指均陷入回调区，较近期高点至少下跌10%，并创下有史以来最大单日点数跌幅。
All three US stock indexes are back in range, down at least 10 per cent from their recent highs and hitting record one-day point drops.
在道指下跌的历史中，2008年四季度跌了19%，2009年一季度再跌13%，2018年四季度跌了11.8%，今年一季度还没有结束，已经跌了9.7%，难怪不少市场人士悲观。
The Dow fell 19% in the fourth quarter of 2008, 13% in the first quarter of 2009, and 11.8% in the fourth quarter of 2018.
但也有投资机构人士认为，从月度、季度走势看，还不能说美国股市已经发生了实质性转变，考虑到2019年以来美股持续上涨，受疫情因素影响而有所回调，也是合乎逻辑的。
But there are also insiders who believe that a substantial shift in US equities cannot be said to have taken place on a monthly or quarterly basis, and that it is logical to take account of the continued rise in U.S. stocks since 2019, which has been influenced by the epidemic.
高盛集团分析师称，标普500指数的回调平均持续四个月，而这一次时间可能更长，主要是考虑到疫情风险的不确定性，以及美联储决策者所面临的限制。
Goldman Sachs Group Inc. analysts say the S & P 500's correction lasted an average of four months, and this time it is likely to be longer, largely because of uncertainty about the risk of the outbreak and the constraints faced by Fed policymakers.
高盛指出，这意味着上周四开始的美股下跌可能要到7月才能触底。
That means the decline in U.S. stocks that began Thursday may not bottom out until July, Goldman notes.
花旗集团策略师也提到了这两个不稳定因素，称标普500指数要跌至2730点才会变得有吸引力，即比其200天移动平均线低10%。
Citigroup strategists also cited both uncertainties, saying the S & P 500 would have to fall to 2,730 to become attractive, 10% below its 200-day moving average.
这意味着标普500指数在目前水平上还要下跌12%。
That means the S & P 500 is down 12% from its current level.
欧股主要股指收盘大跌，英国富时100指数下跌246.07点，跌幅为3.49%，报收于6796.40点。
The main European indexes closed sharply lower, with the FTSE 100 index falling 246.07 points, or 3.49 per cent, to 6,796.40.
德国DAX指数27日下跌407.42点，跌幅为3.19%，报收于12367.46点。
Germany's DAX index fell 407.42 points, or 3.19%, to end at 12367.46.
法国CAC40指数下跌188.95点，跌幅为3.32%，报收于5495.60点。
The French CAC40 fell 188.95 points, or 3.32 per cent, to 5495.60.
此外，富时意大利MIB指数下跌623.17点，跌幅为2.66%。
In addition, the FTSE Italy MIB index fell 623.17 points, or 2.66%.
大宗商品市场方面，WTI原油收跌1.64美元/桶，跌幅3.37%，收报47.09美元/桶。
In commodities, WTI crude fell $1.64 a barrel, or 3.37%, to $47.09 a barrel.
4月交货的伦敦布伦特原油期货价格下跌1.25美元，收于每桶52.18美元，跌幅为2.77%。
London Brent crude for April delivery fell $1.25, or 2.77 per cent, to $52.18 a barrel.
纽约商品交易所黄金期货市场交投最活跃的4月黄金期价下跌0.6美元，收于每盎司1642.5美元，跌幅为0.04%。
Gold futures, the most active trading session on the New York Mercantile Exchange, fell $0.60, or 0.04%, to $1642.5 an ounce in April.
2月28日中国沪深股市开盘后，延续了美欧股市的大幅度下跌态势：上证综指以2924.64点开盘，其后盘中跌破2900点，最低2891.88点，下跌3.3%；深圳成指当天上午下跌4.27%，创业板指数下跌4.87%；香港股市恒生指数当天上午亦下跌2.84%，逼近26000点大关。
After trading opened on Feb. 28, the Shanghai and Shenzhen stock markets continued their sharp declines: the Shanghai Composite Index opened at 2924.64, then fell below 2900 points, or 3.3%, to a low of 2891.88. Shenzhen's Shenzhen index fell 4.27% in the morning and 4.87% in the GEM index.
投资分析人士认为，美欧股市受疫情蔓延冲击，中国股市亦无法独善其身。
Investment analysts believe that U.S. and European stock markets have been hit by the epidemic, China's stock market is not immune.
评级机构穆迪公司（Moody's）旗下穆迪分析（Moody’s Analytics ）首席经济学家马克·赞迪（Mark Zandi）对《财经》记者指出，市场投资者已开始为全球经济衰退定价，至少肆虐的新型冠状病毒会严重影响企业的收益。
Mark Zandi, chief economist at Moody's Analytics, the ratings agency Moody's Analytics, told Caijing that market investors have begun to price the global recession, with at least the new coronavirus wreaking havoc on corporate earnings.
如果冠状肺炎疫情成为全球性的大流行病，经济衰退就难以避免。
If the outbreak of coronary pneumonia becomes a global pandemic, a recession is inevitable.
在接下来的几周里，股市还会有更多糟糕的日子。
In the next few weeks, there will be more bad days in the stock market.
高盛将2020年美国公司基本每股收益预估值从174美元下调至165美元，即在2020年0%增长，并将2021年的预估值从183美元下调至175美元。
Goldman lowered its 2020 estimate of basic earnings per share for U.S. companies to $165 from $174, or 0% in 2020, and lowered its estimate for 2021 to $175 from $183.
高盛首席美国股票策略师戴维-科斯汀(David Kostin)在周四给客户的一份报告中说：“美国公司在2020年将不会实现盈利增长。
David Kostin, chief US equity strategist at Goldman Sachs, said in a note to clients on Thursday: "There will be no profit growth for US companies in 2020.
我们更新了盈利模型，以考虑到该病毒广泛传播的可能性。
We have updated our profit model to take into account the possibility of widespread transmission of the virus.
”据意大利媒体报道，截至目前，意大利累计确诊653例新冠病毒肺炎感染病例；新增5例死亡病例，累计17例死亡病例；累计治愈45例。
So far, Italy has confirmed 653 new cases of pneumonia, five new deaths and 17 cumulative deaths, and 45 cumulative cures, Italian media reported.
在疫情已蔓延至意大利的13个大区的同时；巴西、格鲁吉亚、希腊、北马其顿、挪威、巴基斯坦和罗马尼亚在过去一天内报告了他们的首例“2019年冠状病毒病”病例。
While the epidemic has spread to 13 regions of Italy, Brazil, Georgia, Greece, Northern Macedonia, Norway, Pakistan, and Romania reported their first case of coronavirus 2019 in the past day.
多位华尔街人士对《财经》记者说，全球肆虐的新型冠状病毒可能会遏制全球经济增长，原因是各国与疫情斗争的主要方式是对整个地区进行隔离，这意味着货物流通受阻。
A number of Wall Street people told Caijing that the new coronavirus raging around the world could curb global economic growth because the main way countries are fighting the epidemic is by isolating entire regions, which means the movement of goods is blocked.
全球经济的相互联系，可以预见全球贸易下降，经济增长会停滞。
The interconnectedness of the global economy could foresee a decline in global trade and stagnation in economic growth.
这转而会打击消费。
This, in turn, depresses consumption.
美联储前主席耶伦表示，在全球肆虐的新型冠状病毒可能会遏制全球经济增长，甚至可能导致美国经济衰退。
Former Federal Reserve Chairman Janet Yellen says the new coronavirus raging around the world could choke off global economic growth and could even lead to a US recession.
耶伦周三在智库布鲁金斯学会的一次活动中表示：“这是可以想象的，可能会使美国陷入衰退。
"This is conceivable and could plunge the United States into recession," Yellen said at an event Wednesday at the Brookings Institution, a think tank.
” 经济衰退的广泛定义是国内生产总值（GDP）连续两个季度下降。
A recession is broadly defined as a fall in gross domestic product (GDP) for two consecutive quarters.
世界卫生组织总干事谭德塞2月27日的表示：如果有任何国家认为本国不会受到新冠疫情侵袭，那将是一个“致命错误”，所有国家都应做好应对措施。
Any country that believes it will not be hit by the new crown would be a "fatal mistake" and all countries should be prepared to respond, said World Health Organisation Director General Theresa Tupper on February 27.
在于日内瓦举行的记者会上表示，“每个国家都应做好准备，应对第一个病例、第一组集群病例、社区传播的第一个证据以及持续的社区传播”，“任何国家都不应想当然地认为不会出现这种情况。
"Every country should be prepared to deal with the first case, the first cluster of cases, the first evidence of community transmission, and sustained community transmission," said a press conference in Geneva. "No country should take it for granted that this will not happen.
这将会是一个致命的错误。
That would be a fatal mistake.
这种病毒没有国界。
The virus knows no borders.
”因初级保健内科的开创性工作而闻名于世的哈佛医学院和麻省总院的全科医学终身教授阿伦·高路（Allen Goroll）对《财经》记者说，疫情的经验教训其实我们都知道，就是疫情早期报告和全面公共卫生应对的重要性。
Allen Goroll, a life-long professor of general medicine at Harvard Medical School and Massachusetts Institute of Medicine, who is renowned for his pioneering work in primary health care, told Caijing that the lessons we all know are the importance of early reporting of the outbreak and a comprehensive public health response.
谭德塞说，伊朗、意大利和韩国的疫情正处于一个“决定性的时刻”，这三个国家的疫情表明了这种病毒的能力。
He said the outbreaks in Iran, Italy and South Korea are at a "decisive moment," and that the outbreaks in the three countries demonstrate the virus's ability.
他还表示，这种病毒具有成为“全球流行病的潜力”，“现在不是恐惧的时候。
He also said the virus had the potential to become "a global epidemic" and that "this is not a time for fear."
现在是采取行动预防感染和拯救生命的时候”，“只要采取正确的措施，疫情是可以得到控制的”。
Now is the time to take action to prevent infection and save lives, "he said." With the right measures, the outbreak can be contained. "
